Abike Dabiri-Erewa, Chairman/CEO, Nigerians in Diaspora Commission (NIDCOM) has described the sudden death of Michael Ojo, a Nigerian basketball player, as saddening and shocking. Ojo, a Nigerian basketball player, died on Friday during a training session with Red Star at the age of 27 years. Dabiri-Erewa in her condolence message, she said the news of the sudden death of the promising basketball player in Serbia during training was painful. The NIDCOM boss regretted that Michael, 27, died in his prime when he was about to launch himself into global arena and using his God-given talent to promote the image of Nigeria abroad. She commiserated with Ojoâ€™s family, his club, Red Star, and the country at large on the loss of another rising star in the country. Dabiri-Erewa prayed unto God to give his family the fortitude to bear the irreplaceable loss and for God to accept his soul to rest in perfect peace.